rology and neurosurgery departments throughout Canada, the United States, Europe, Asia, and Latin America. Recounting the story of one of Canada’s greatest contributions to international medical science through archival research, personal interviews, photographs, illustrations, and paintings, The Wounded Brain Healed provides fascinating insight into the institution that had a global and lasting impact.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBrainxDiseasesxPatientsxCarexHistoryxQuébec (Province)xMontréal. 0aBrainxDiseasesxPatientsxCarezQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aBrainxDiseasesxPatientsxCarezQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aBrainxResearchxHistoryxQuébec (Province)xMontréal. 0aBrainxResearchzQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aBrainxResearchzQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aCentres de recherchexHistoirexQuébec (Province)xMontréal. 0aCerveauxMaladiesxPatientsxSoinsxHistoirexQuébec (Province)xMontréal. 0aCerveauxRecherchexHistoirexQuébec (Province)xMontréal. 0aNeurosciencesxRecherchexHistoirexQuébec (Province)xMontréal. 0aNeurosciencesxResearchxHistoryxQuébec (Province)xMontréal. 0aNeurosciencesxResearchzQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aNeurosciencesxResearchzQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aResearch institutesxHistoryxQuébec (Province)xMontréal. 0aResearch instituteszQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 0aResearch instituteszQuébec (Province)zMontréalxHistory. 7aMEDICAL / History.2bisacsh1 aAdams, Annmarie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntel, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeindel, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeblanc, Richard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/